<br>
Funny....but Ely's absolutly right. Odd that not more people see it.<br>
<br>
The original vision was that players would literally whack through the mobs. In basic terms, the way any given guild fights boss mobs, was how we were &quot;SUPPOSED&quot; to engage every mob. (Idiot terms - Verant NEVER considered the fact that players might &quot;pull&quot;)<br>
<br>
Knowing this, take a look at the difference between the old world and Luclin. The old world is relatively safe to walk through, really, where in Luclin, its not. It was actually stated that they based Luclin around the original vision, only with &quot;pulling&quot; in mind. Now, we can still pull in Luclin, but its a liiiiiittle tougher, and a lot harder to loaf around or walk through a zone unrisked.<br>
<br>
Basically, Luclin is a different playstyle than old world. The one we grew up in. Perhaps we adapted to Luclin, then unknowingly applied it to the old world and we dont see the difference for what it really is, but its there.<br>
<br>
Changes to classes, however....is a much more drastic thing.<br>
<br>
Its abrupt, and it leaves us (in this case, monks) with a feeling of nowhere to go. If anything, pray its not that major of a change, otherwise, I truly feel for the monks.<br>
<br>
I'd say the same for guilds, with the mod rod nerf, but Im confident that guilds will work around this.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, Ely's right. We shouldnt have played for 3 years, fine tuning our moves, only to be told &quot;All that shit you learned...unlearn it, we fucked up. Our bad.&quot;<br>
